  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN209-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – atu. tuṟai – paricilkaṭāaṉilai. avaṉparicil nīṭṭittāṉaip peruntalaiccāttaṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div xml:id="PN209">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>poykai nārai pōrviṟ cēkku</l>
<l>neytalaṅ kaḻaṉi nellari toḻuvar</l>
<l>kūmpuviṭu meṉpiṇi yaviḻnta vāmpa</l>
<l>lakalaṭai yariyaṉ māntit teṇkaṭaṟ</l>
<l>paṭutirai yiṉcīrp pāṇi tūṅku</l>
<l>meṉpulam vaippi ṉaṉṉāṭṭup poruna</l>
<l>palkaṉi nacaii yalkuvicum pukantu</l>
<l>perumalai viṭarakañ cilampa muṉṉip</l>
<l>paḻaṉuṭaip perumaran tīrnteṉak kaiyaṟṟup</l>
<l>peṟātu peyarum puḷḷiṉam pōlaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉacaitara vantuniṉ ṉicainuval paricilēṉ</l>
<l>vaṟuviyēṉ peyarkō vāṇmēm paṭuna</l>
<l>vīyā yāyiṉu miraṅkuve ṉallē</l>
<l>ṉōyilai yākumati peruma nammuṭ</l>
<l>kuṟunaṇi kāṇkuva tāka nāḷu</l>
<l>naṟumpa lolivaruṅ katuppiṉ ṭēmoḻit</l>
<l>teriyiḻai makaḷir pāṇi pārkkum</l>
<l>peruvarai yaṉṉa mārpiṟ</l>
<l>ceruveñ cēeyniṉ makiḻiruk kaiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="6">O fighter of a good land in the region of soft soil, </l>
<l corresp="2">where the paddy-cutting workmen in the paddy fields with blue waterlilies </l>
<l corresp="1">on heaps of which the herons from the pond rest, </l>
<l corresp="4a-c">feed on toddy from the wide leaves </l>
<l corresp="3">of white waterlilies that opened [their] soft outer petals to release the closed [buds] </l>
<l corresp="4d-5">[and] sway to the pleasing measured rhythm of the clear sea’s dashing waves, </l>
<l corresp="10cd">like a flock of birds that, </l>
<l corresp="7">yearning for many ripe fruit, ascend the sky where they stay, </l>
<l corresp="8">approach a big mountain so that the inside of caves resound, </l>
<l corresp="9">are prostrate because the big tree that had fruit had coe to an end, </l>
<l corresp="10ab">  [and] return without having obtained [anything], </l>
<l corresp="11">having come yearning for you, shall I, a gift-seeker uttering your fame </l>
<l corresp="12">return a poor man? O you who excel with the sword </l>
<l corresp="13">even if you won’t give I will not lament. </l>
<l corresp="14">Be without pain, great man. Among us, </l>
<l corresp="15a-c">it being seen in near proximity, </l>
<l corresp="19">there is the delightful seat of you, [like] the Red one, hot in fight, </l>
<l corresp="18">with a chest like a big mountain, </l>
<l corresp="17">for whose beat women with clear jewels look, </l>
<l corresp="16">with sweet words, [their] hair sprouting in many fragrant [curls], </l>
<l corresp="15d">daily. </l>
</lg>
